      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The desire to have control when everything feels out of reach is a deep and understandable ache. When the physical self betrays you, the feeling of losing agency is terrifying. If the idea of control feels completely gone, perhaps finding a small, immediate way to reclaim *some* power is possible. Even making a small decision about what to eat or what to watch can be a tiny act of defiance against the helplessness.",
